## Explanation:

### Solution 01

- Using ***Recursive Dynamic Programming - Memoization.***
- **Remember while initializing the array with 10001, if we do 1001 then it will give the wrong answer for large values.**
- We take a dp array to store recursive solutions.
- Help array for the recursion, base case when start index is greater than size of the array.
- From 1 to the num position we’ll calculate the minimum value & update the dp array.
- Finally return the value dp[start].
- **Time complexity:** O(n^2).

