The idea is a small extension to Inorder iterative traversal.

Here's the iterative inorder traversal:
```
public List < Integer > inorderTraversal(TreeNode root) {
        List < Integer > res = new ArrayList < > ();
        Stack < TreeNode > stack = new Stack < > ();
        TreeNode curr = root;
        while (curr != null || !stack.isEmpty()) {
            while (curr != null) {
                stack.push(curr);
                curr = curr.left;
            }
            curr = stack.pop();
            res.add(curr.val);
            curr = curr.right;
        }
        return res;
    }
```
For post order traversal:
So, while moving to the left most node, we also add the curr roots right to the stack along with the curr node.
Then when we reach the left most node, if it doesn't have any right node (i.e it is a leaf node), we add it to result and set curr to null. 

Else, if the curr node's right node is same as the stack's top., this means that the current's right tree is yet to be processed. So, before processing curr, we have to process its right subtree., so, we pop the right node from stack, push curr to the stack and point curr to its right node and continue with processing.
```
public List<Integer> postorderTraversal(TreeNode root) {
        TreeNode curr = root;
        Stack<TreeNode> stack = new Stack<>();

        List<Integer> res = new ArrayList<>();

        while (curr != null || !stack.isEmpty()) {
            while (curr != null) {
			    // push right on to stack before curr
                if (curr.right != null) stack.push(curr.right);
				//push curr onto stack and move left
                stack.push(curr);
                curr = curr.left;
            }

            curr = stack.pop();

            // if curr's right is at the top of stack i.e, it is not yet processed
            if (!stack.isEmpty() && curr.right == stack.peek()) {
			    //pop its right from stack
                stack.pop();
				//push curr to stack to process it in future
                stack.push(curr);
				//point curr to its right
                curr = curr.right;
            }
            else {
			    // if curr is left most and doesnt have any right or if its right has already been processed, process curr and set it to null
                res.add(curr.val);
                curr = null;
            }
        }

        return res;
    }
```

