## Postorder Iterative
Postorder traversal is first left then right then parent i.e. **L R P**
L --> Left
R --> Right
P --> Parent
* We have to get **L R P** but we can get **P R L** easily then we can reverse the **ans vector** we will get **L R P**.
* In **stack** push first **root** then run **while loop** till **stack** is **not empty**. Inside while every iteration take top of stack node i.e. **curr = stk.top()** and then **pop** stack.
* First **push_back** value of **curr** in **ans** vector then **push left** in stack after that **push right** in stack if left and right are **not NULL**.
* *Why are we pushing left then right ?* Ans: Because when we **pop** from **stack** it will give **right** then **left** and our desire is **P R L** only. If we push **L** then **R** stack will give reverse **R** then **L**.

```
	vector<int> postorderTraversal(TreeNode* root) {
		vector<int> ans;
		if(root==NULL)
			return ans;

		TreeNode* curr;
		stack<TreeNode*> st;
		st.push(root);
		while(!st.empty()){
			curr = st.top();
			st.pop();
			ans.push_back(curr->val); // Take ans
			if(curr->left)  // Push left first
				st.push(curr->left);
			if(curr->right)  // Push right first
				st.push(curr->right);
		}
		reverse(ans.begin(),ans.end()); // reverse ans to get L R P
		return ans;
	}
```

## Preorder Iterative
* Preorder is **P L R**.
* For this we first take ans of curr then we can push right (**R**) in stack then push left (**L**) in **stack** that makes pop in reverse order that is **L** then **R**.
* Here no need to reverse ans because our desire goal is **P L R** only.

