First we'll convert the string into list. Applying the two pointer approach here, first we take the ```start``` pointer and the ```end``` pointer. When both have same values we swap their values and move both by 1. ```start += 1``` and ```end -=1```. If any value is not vowels move the pointer forward by 1.

